# Byte-identical checkouts on every OS.
#
# The corpus and the adapters are inputs to a determinism benchmark: their
# BYTES are part of the experiment's controlled variables. Without this file,
# GitHub's Windows runners check out with CRLF (core.autocrlf=true) while
# Linux and macOS check out LF, so the three CI machines were benchmarking
# corpora that were never byte-identical. Fingerprint format 2 records a
# corpus content hash and exposed exactly that: NOT COMPARABLE, corpus content
# d157a88a... (LF) vs 9555e43c... (CRLF).
* text=auto eol=lf

*.png -text
*.ico -text
*.svg text eol=lf
